# Purpose

Implement an approved feature plan with focused subagent help.

# Required Inputs

- `agent-workflow/artifacts/PLAN.md`
- `agent-workflow/artifacts/FILE_SPECS.md`
- `agent-workflow/artifacts/DECISION.md` when prior choices exist

# Workflow

1. Read `PLAN.md`, `FILE_SPECS.md`, and `DECISION.md` if it exists.
2. If planning artifacts are missing or too vague, stop and ask the user to run `$plan-feature` first.
3. This skill requires Codex multi-agent. If multi-agent is unavailable, stop and tell the user to run `/multi-agent` and start a new Codex session before retrying.
4. Before editing application code, spawn at least one focused subagent for repository exploration or an isolated implementation slice.
5. When multiple subagents edit code, keep their ownership disjoint so integration stays straightforward.
6. Wait for the required subagent results before integrating dependent changes in the parent session.
7. Implement the approved plan.
8. If multiple viable strategies appear during implementation, stop for user choice and append the decision to `DECISION.md`.
9. For Next.js-specific implementation details, use `next-best-practices` when relevant.
10. For React performance or rendering issues, use `vercel-react-best-practices` when relevant.
11. For component system work, use `building-components` or `vercel-composition-patterns` when relevant.
12. Spawn the agent named `verifier` and wait for it to update `agent-workflow/artifacts/VERIFY.md`.
13. Spawn the agent named `reviewer` and wait for it to update `agent-workflow/artifacts/REVIEW.md`.

# Guardrails

- Do not fall back to a single-agent implementation when the required subagents cannot be spawned; stop instead.
- Keep changes aligned with the approved plan unless the user approves a plan change.
- Reference workflow artifacts in the final summary.
- Keep verification and review as separate spawned closeout steps, not hidden work.
